label.value: Ascorbic acid/Selenium/Vitamin E
Rheumatoid Nodule

value.value: A well circumscribed lump of tissue, firm to touch, typically non-tender, predominantly occurring as a cutaneous manifestation of rheumatoid arthritis localized to extensor surfaces near joints, but may be internal.

label.value: Systemic Juvenile Idiopathic Arthritis

value.value: A category of juvenile idiopathic arthritis defined by the presence of arthritis and high fevers, and accompanied by at least 2 of the following systemic features: lymphadenopathy, organomegaly, rash, or serositis. Macrophage activation syndrome is a well known complication.

label.value: Oligoarticular Juvenile Idiopathic Arthritis

value.value: A category of juvenile idiopathic arthritis defined by the presence of arthritis affecting between one and four separate joints during the first six months of disease.

label.value: Polyarticular Juvenile Idiopathic Arthritis, Rheumatoid Factor Negative

value.value: A category of juvenile idiopathic arthritis defined by the presence of arthritis affecting five or more separate joints during the first six months of disease, with negative serologic testing for rheumatoid factor.

label.value: Polyarticular Juvenile Idiopathic Arthritis, Rheumatoid Factor Positive

value.value: A category of juvenile idiopathic arthritis defined by the presence of arthritis affecting five or more separate joints during the first six months of disease, with positive serologic testing for rheumatoid factor.

label.value: Undifferentiated Juvenile Idiopathic Arthritis

value.value: A category of juvenile idiopathic arthritis that does not fulfill any single category or has criteria for more than one category.

label.value: Early Localized Lyme Disease

value.value: An early stage of Lyme disease that may present within 3-30 days after a tick bite with a red, concentrically-expanding rash (erythema migrans), fatigue, chills, fever, headache, muscle and joint aches, and swollen lymph nodes.

label.value: Early Disseminated Lyme Disease

value.value: An early stage of Lyme disease that may present days to weeks after a tick bite with relapsing signs of a red, concentrically-expanding rash (erythema migrans), facial palsy, meningismus, neuralgia, heart palpitations, and dizziness.

label.value: Late Disseminated Lyme Disease

value.value: A late stage of Lyme disease that may present in untreated patients months to years after a tick bite manifested with intermittent bouts of arthralgia, arthritis and neurologic complaints.

label.value: Post-Treatment Lyme Disease Syndrome

value.value: A constellation of symptoms lasting months to years reported by some Lyme disease patients who had undergone previous antibiotic therapy.

label.value: Flavopiridol/irinotecan
Persistent Oligoarticular Juvenile Idiopathic Arthritis

value.value: Oligoarticular juvenile idiopathic arthritis that never involves more than four separate joints after six months.

label.value: Extended Oligoarticular Juvenile Idiopathic Arthritis

value.value: Oligoarticular juvenile idiopathic arthritis that eventually involves more than four separate joints.

label.value: Chronic Recurrent Multifocal Osteomyelitis

value.value: An autoinflammatory disease characterized by sterile bone lesions which are multifocal and/or recurrent.

label.value: NALP12-Associated Hereditary Periodic Fever Syndrome

value.value: An autoinflammatory disease caused by mutations in the NLRP12 gene. It is characterized by periodic fevers beginning in the first year of life that are triggered by cold exposure. Episodes occur more than once per month.

label.value: Psoriatic Juvenile Idiopathic Arthritis

value.value: A category of juvenile idiopathic arthritis defined by the presence of arthritis with a personal or family history of psoriasis, and features such as dactylitis and nail dystrophy.

label.value: Early Rheumatoid Arthritis

value.value: Recent diagnosis of rheumatoid arthritis (usually within one to two years of onset) during which treatment may be more effective and possibly improve the disease course.

label.value: Scleritis

value.value: Inflammation of the sclera.

label.value: Erythema Migrans

value.value: A red, concentrically-expanding rash sometimes with central clearing, that is part of the first stage of Lyme disease caused by infection with Borrelia species.

label.value: Pain Amplification Syndrome

value.value: A condition in which the nerves register normal stimuli (lack of tissue injury) as pain, resulting in feelings of intense pain with even minor sensory input.

label.value: Synovitis, Acne, Pustulosis, Hyperostosis, and Osteitis Syndrome

value.value: A syndrome characterized by synovitis, acne, pustulosis, hyperostosis, and non-infectious osteomyelitis. Includes a spectrum of aseptic neutrophilic dermatoses associated with aseptic osteoarticular lesions.

label.value: Indium In 111 Monoclonal Antibody Bre-3/Yttrium Y 90 Monoclonal Antibody Bre-3
Autoinflammatory Syndrome

value.value: A group of disorders of the innate immune system characterized by attacks of seemingly unprovoked inflammation without significant levels of either autoantibodies or autoreactive T cells more characteristic of autoimmune disease.

label.value: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor 1-Associated Periodic Syndrome

value.value: An autoinflammatory disease caused by mutations in the TNFRSF1A gene coding for tumor necrosis factor receptor 1 (TNFR1). This results in attacks of fever, rash, peritoneal, pleural, or pericardial serositis and/or synovial inflammation along with increased acute phase reactants. Complications may include amyloidosis.

label.value: Familial Cold Autoinflammatory Syndrome

value.value: An autoinflammatory disease caused by mutations in the NLRP3 gene which encodes cryopyrin. It is characterized by short episodes of fever, rash, and arthralgia after exposure to cold or rapid decrease in temperature.

label.value: Muckle-Wells Syndrome

value.value: An autoinflammatory disease caused by mutations in the NLRP3 gene which encodes cryopyrin. It is characterized by recurrent episodes of urticaria and fever which develop in infancy. It may lead to sensorineural hearing loss and/or amyloidosis.

label.value: Pyogenic Arthritis, Pyoderma Gangrenosum and Acne

value.value: An autoinflammatory disease caused by mutations in the PSTPIP1 gene. It is characterized by episodes of destructive arthritis, ulcerative skin lesions and cystic acne.

label.value: Deficiency of the Interleukin-1 Receptor Antagonist

value.value: An autoinflammatory disease caused by mutations in the IL1RN gene, which encodes the IL1 receptor antagonist. It presents in infancy, and is characterized by systemic inflammation, pustular rash, bone pain, sterile osteitis, and periostitis.

label.value: Deficiency of the Interleukin-36 Receptor Antagonist

value.value: An autoinflammatory disease caused by mutations in the IL36RN gene, which encodes the IL36 receptor antagonist. It is characterized by periodic fevers and psoriasiform rash.

label.value: Majeed Syndrome

value.value: An autoinflammatory disease caused by mutations in the LPIN2 gene. It is characterized by early-onset chronic recurrent multifocal osteomyelitis, congenital dyserythropoietic anemia and inflammatory dermatosis.
